ssages containing all keywords: \'transport\', \'Error\', \'while\', \'dialing\' in close proximity.\\nCheck Log: Search for the keyword \'unavailable\' (case-insensitive) in log messages.\\nCheck Metric: Query the `pod_processes` metric for pods belonging to the \'adservice\' service and compare the p99 value during the fault window against the normal baseline.",\n    "Fault Type: pod_cpu_usage\\nSymptom: JVM CPU usage spike and overload, leading to service latency increase.\\nRoot Cause: Component [adservice] experienced [pod_cpu_usage] fault, accompanied by [adservice--stress] anomaly.\\nReasoning: Step 1: Check Metadata - Confirm faulty component is [adservice] (From Ground Truth). Step 2: Check Observation - Found keyword [adservice--stress] in Log (From GT key_observations). Step 3: Check Observation - Found keyword [invocationtargetexception] in Log (From GT key_observations). Step 4: Check Observation - Found keyword [transformlistener] in Log (From GT key_observations). Step 5: Check Observation - Found keyword [frontend] in Trace (subtype: latency_anomalies) (From GT key_observations). Step 6: Check Observation - Found keyword [pod_cpu_usage] in Metric (From GT key_observations). Step 7: Check Observation - Found keyword [rrt] and [rrt_max] in Metric (From GT key_observations). Step 8: Derive Root Cause - Based on the combined features (stress injection logs and correlated CPU/metric anomalies), determined cause is [pod_cpu_usage] (From Ground Truth).\\nActionable Checks:\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'AdService--stress\' in Log data to confirm stress test injection activity.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'InvocationTargetException\' in Log data to confirm JVM agent attachment errors.\\nCheck Log: Search for keyword \'injectTriggerPoint\' or related terms in Log data to confirm bytecode transformation activity.\\nCheck Trace: Analyze Trace data for latency anomalies on call paths involving \'frontend\' as the caller and \'adservice\' as the callee.\\